  "time_ut": 1660491733,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dca \u0d91\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 - \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0db6\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dca\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cope Eran - Cope Kabir",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Samagi Jana Balawegaya MP Eran Wickramaratne is to be appointed as the Chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Public Affairs (COPE Committee) of the Third House of the Ninth Parliament and Mr. Kabir Hashim of the same party is to be appointed as the Chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Public Accounts (COPE Committee). Parliamentary sources say.",
        "In this regard, in an inquiry made to the chief organizer of our opposition, Mr. Lakshman Kiriella, a lawyer, he said that proposals have been submitted in this regard.",
        "Professor Charita Herath, a member of parliament appointed by the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna, served as the chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Public Affairs in the second chamber of the Ninth Parliament.",
        "Professor Tissa Witharana previously worked as the Chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Public Accounts.",
        "COPE and COPA are the two main committees of the Parliament that conduct investigations and make recommendations on corruption, fraud, irregularities and abuses in public institutions.",
        "The chief organizer of the opposition, Mr. Lawyer Lakshman Kiriella, recently requested the speaker at the committee meeting on parliamentary affairs to give the chairmanship of all the committees of the parliament to the members of the opposition.",
        "At that time, it has been learned that the speaker clearly agreed to it.",
        "The Parliamentary Committee of Selection recently decided to appoint Dr. Harsha De Silva, a Member of the Opposition, as the Chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Finance.",
        "According to parliamentary sources, some of the committees (almost seventy in number) which were abolished with the conclusion of the second session of the Ninth Parliament have been appointed and the rest of the committees will be appointed in the coming days."
      ],
